"title": "4134: demons, exorcism of",
"media_type": "Text",
"index_reference": "4134",
"language": "eng",
"review_level": "None",
"content": "<p>Jesus Christ drove out many demons during his earthly ministry and he delegated this authority to his disciples.</p>\n<h2>Jesus Christ understood exorcism as part of his ministry</h2>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Luke13:32\">LUK 13:32</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Luke4:18\">LUK 4:18</a></p>\n<h3>He drove out demons from individuals brought to him</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Matt8:16\">MAT 8:16</a></strong> parallels <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Mark1:32-Mark1:34\">MRK 1:32–1:34</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Luke4:40-Luke4:41\">LUK 4:40–4:41</a> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Matt4:24\">MAT 4:24</a></p>\n<h3>He drove out demons from individuals whom he encountered</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Mark1:23-Mark1:26\">MRK 1:23–1:26</a></strong> parallel <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Luke4:33-Luke4:35\">LUK 4:33–4:35</a> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Mark1:39\">MRK 1:39</a></p>\n<h2>Jesus Christ had power over demons</h2>\n<h3>He was able to drive demons out at a distance</h3>\n<p><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Matt15:22-Matt15:28\">MAT 15:22–15:28</a> parallel <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Mark7:25-Mark7:30\">MRK 7:25–7:30</a></p>\n<h3>He used words of rebuke to drive out demons</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Matt17:18\">MAT 17:18</a></strong> parallels <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Mark9:25\">MRK 9:25</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Luke9:42\">LUK 9:42</a> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Mark1:25\">MRK 1:25</a> parallel <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Luke4:35\">LUK 4:35</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Luke4:41\">LUK 4:41</a></p>\n<h2>Jesus Christ identifies the spiritual resources needed for exorcising demons</h2>\n<h3>The Spirit of God</h3>\n<p><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Matt12:28\">MAT 12:28</a> parallel <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Luke11:20\">LUK 11:20</a></p>\n<h3>Faith</h3>\n<p><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Matt17:19-Matt17:20\">MAT 17:19–17:20</a></p>\n<h3>Prayer (and fasting)</h3>\n<p><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Mark9:28-Mark9:29\">MRK 9:28–9:29</a></p>\n<h2>The ministry of exorcism was an indication of the kingdom's presence</h2>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Matt12:28\">MAT 12:28</a></strong> parallel <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Luke11:20\">LUK 11:20</a></p>\n<h2>The results of being delivered from demon-possession</h2>\n<h3>Visible transformation and healing</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Mark5:15\">MRK 5:15</a></strong> parallel <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Luke8:35\">LUK 8:35</a> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Matt9:33\">MAT 9:33</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Luke11:14\">LUK 11:14</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Luke13:13\">LUK 13:13</a></p>\n<h3>Devotion to Jesus Christ</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Luke8:1-Luke8:2\">LUK 8:1–8:2</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Mark5:18\">MRK 5:18</a> parallel <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Luke8:38\">LUK 8:38</a></p>\n<h3>Loss of supernatural faculties</h3>\n<p><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Acts16:16-Acts16:19\">ACT 16:16–16:19</a></p>\n<h3>Demons seek to return</h3>\n<p><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Matt12:43-Matt12:45\">MAT 12:43–12:45</a> parallel <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Luke11:24-Luke11:26\">LUK 11:24–11:26</a></p>\n<h2>The impact of exorcism on those who observe it</h2>\n<h3>Amazement</h3>\n<p><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Matt9:33\">MAT 9:33</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Matt12:23\">MAT 12:23</a>; ; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Mark1:27\">MRK 1:27</a> parallel <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Luke4:36\">LUK 4:36</a>; ; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Luke11:14\">LUK 11:14</a></p>\n<h3>Fear</h3>\n<p><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Matt8:34\">MAT 8:34</a> parallels <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Mark5:17\">MRK 5:17</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Luke8:37\">LUK 8:37</a></p>",
